{
  "id": "11",
  "name": "Remove Unwanted Characters Advanced",
  "description": "This node removes unwanted characters",
  "input": "It accepts a DataFrame as input from the previous Node",
  "type": "transform",
  "engine": "all",
  "nodeClass": "fire.nodes.etl.NodeRemoveUnwantedCharactersMultiple",
  "fields" : [
    {"name":"inputCols", "value": "[]", "widget": "variables_list_select", "title": "Input Columns", "description": "Input columns"},

    {"name": "removeWhitespaces", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_array", "title": "Remove Whitespaces", "optionsArray": ["true","false"],
            "description": "Removes white space"},

    {"name": "removeLetters", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_array", "title": "Remove Letters", "optionsArray": ["true","false"],
            "description": "Removes letters"},

    {"name": "removeDigits", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_array", "title": "Remove Digits", "optionsArray": ["true","false"],
            "description": "Removes digits"},

    {"name": "removeSigns", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_array", "title": "Remove Signs", "optionsArray": ["true","false"],
            "description": "Removes signs"},

    {"name": "removeCommas", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_array", "title": "Remove Commas", "optionsArray": ["true","false"],
      "description": "Removes commas"}

  ]
}

start-details:

This node removes unwanted characters from the specified input columns

end-details:

start-examples:

Incoming Dataframe has following row:

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | $12,500.00 |  Salary hiked by 10%

If removeunwantedcharactersmultiple is configured to remove unwanted characters [SIGNS] & [COMMAS] from [SALARY] & [DIGITS] and [SIGNS] from [COMMENTS] columns 
then outgoing Dataframe would result as below:

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | 1250000    |  Salary hiked by 

Below examples detail how data is processed based on selected options

h2:REMOVE WHITESPACES is selected as [True]

Whitespaces are removed from the selected columns [SALARY] and [COMMENTS]

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | $12,500.00 |  Salaryhikedby10%
 
h2:REMOVE LETTERS is selected as [True]

Alphabets are removed from the selected columns [SALARY] and [COMMENTS]

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | $12,500.00 |  10%

h2:REMOVE DIGITS is selected as [True]

Numbers are removed from the selected columns [SALARY] and [COMMENTS]

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | $,.        |  Salary hiked by %
 
h2:REMOVE SIGNS is selected as [True]

Special characters are removed from the selected columns [SALARY] and [COMMENTS]

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | 1250000    |  Salary hiked by 10
 
h2:REMOVE COMMAS is selected as [True]

Commas are removed from the selected columns [SALARY] and [COMMENTS]

 CUST_CD  |  CUST_NAME  |  SALARY    |    COMMENTS          
-------------------------------------------------------------
 C01      |  MIKE       | $12500.00  |  Salary hiked by 10%

end-examples:
